	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 3rd 11:38 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>BOO YA!&nbsp;&nbsp;Once again, the great Tallicus is right!  I looked it up in the FAQ and found out that my little theory about the whole "scholar mystery" was correct.  User is the name given to anyone with a "karma" (average of all scores) lower than 3 and a scholar is anywhere from 3-3.5.  Then at 3.6 you become a "sage", then after a certain karma is reached you are a "guru".  I'm not sure on those numbers (actually I'm almost certain they are wrong), but you get the point.  Go to the FAQ (link at the very bottom of the page) to see the real numbers.<br>&nbsp;<br>"We are not hermits.&nbsp;&nbsp;We who would rather have a decaying corpse fighting at our side then to have you and your stench within a mile of us."  -Me on Necros...  there's a lot more but it's a sig.</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
