<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100217782178105></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100217782178105><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100217782178105>RE: Scholar?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=100217782178105#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>224 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 4th 2:43 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>ACK! You certainly are back in business! Wow...you've almost convinced me barbs are the king. But I don't give that easily =P. First off, whatever I believe and say about races/stats for rogues, I am a complete idiot for not following my own advice. I first made a dwarf rogue cuz I wanted something better than a human but wanted him around the same area. Being the foolish newbie I was, I listened to idiots and the EQ manual's advice and put my stat points into mostly AGI and DEX. So my starting dorf rogue was 95 STR, 95 STA, 93 AGI, 107 DEX. My figuring was that DEX is the most important stat for rogues and that AGI was almost as important; so I thought I had a great well-rounded rogue with a head start in his best stat. Still believing AGI and DEX were the best stats, I proceeded to gobble up as many AGI and DEX items as I could find in auctions. I soon had 115 AGI and a very nice 147 DEX (untwinked, mind you). But my STR and STA were both only 98. Even with all these blunders, my rogue still kicks a*s over any other rogue of the same level I group with. If I had followed my preaching, I would own the world!! (or not). Anyway, you don't have to do anything to convince me STR is best for rogues; I've come to learn that and I'm trying to correct my errors and get STR items. The problem is I don't believe AGI is useful. In your calculation of barbs having 5 more points than dorfs, you include AGI. You suggest making AGI 92 just to match it with the barb's, but that's a whole 12 points wasted. What I WOULD do if I could go back and recreate Daviv (I don't wanna start another character right now...I hate newbies too much to be one again) is probably dump 15 into each STR and DEX and end up with 105 and 115. Oh, and you can't just dump all 30 points into DEX. You can put a maximum of 25 bonus points into any one stat. So I'm guessing you'd dump 25 into your barbie's DEX then 5 into STR, for 108 STR 105 DEX. In that case I'd match the dorf's STR to the barb's and put the other 12 into DEX, for 108 STR 112 DEX. I could even match the 95 STA and still have 107 DEX, just to show off. The AGI is still 12 less, but I don't worry about that. If I were going for even capability in offense and defense, I'd be all for Barbie dolls. But as it is I intend to make the best offensive melee unit possible, the dorf rogue. In the end though, 5 points (actually 7 points; in favor of the dorf) doesn't matter all that much. Just don't go DE anyone! Oh and thanks for the info on the karma. I never knew there was an FAQ before...now I've gotta thank you by rating you as Awf... I mean Excellent. ;)<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD 28th Dwarf Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></tr>
